rComments: Lot of work, but you do get a lot out of it.  Daniel is helpful, albeit a bit anal, and he organizes the class so that everything is manageable.  Definitely recommend him as an instructor.
a lot of work and ridiculous expectations for a college student.

The class is a lot of work but you will learn a great deal.  He takes a real interest in the topic and the information that he shares.  He asks you to apply the theories to your research and your life.  So the course is more than retaining the info for a test. It is actually knowing and applying.  You are able to think through your research.
